# Project Context Rule (MANDATORY)

Before generating any code, UI, architecture, or product decisions, you MUST always reference and align with the following documents located in /docs:

## Required Context Files (always load first)
1. /docs/company-context.md
2. /docs/MLDS-4_0-Reference.md
3. /docs/moneylion-project-instructions.md
4. /docs/moneylion-workflow-instructions.md

---

## Strict Rules

### 1. Always read context first
You must treat the 4 files above as the source of truth before:
- Writing any code
- Designing any UI
- Making product decisions
- Suggesting architecture
- Modifying existing flows

If any instruction conflicts with your prior assumptions, the docs override everything.

---

### 2. No execution without context alignment
If a request is missing alignment with these documents, you must:
- Pause implementation logic
- Infer missing requirements from the 4 docs first
- Ensure consistency with system design, UX patterns, and workflows defined there

---

### 3. Design system compliance (mandatory)
All UI must:
- Use components defined in /docs/MLDS-4_0-Reference.md
- Follow spacing, typography, and interaction rules strictly
- Avoid introducing new patterns unless explicitly justified

---

### 4. Product behavior consistency
All features must:
- Align with business logic in /docs/company-context.md
- Respect user flows defined in /docs/moneylion-project-instructions.md
- Follow process rules in /docs/moneylion-workflow-instructions.md

---

### 5. No redundant assumptions
Do NOT:
- Re-define product behavior already described in docs
- Invent alternative workflows without checking existing ones
- Override system rules for convenience

---

### 6. Resolution priority order
When conflicts appear, follow this hierarchy:

1. company-context.md (business logic)
2. moneylion-project-instructions.md (product rules)
3. moneylion-workflow-instructions.md (process execution rules)
4. MLDS-4_0-Reference.md (UI implementation rules)

---

### 7. Output discipline
All outputs must:
- Be consistent with the above documents
- Avoid contradicting established flows
- Use existing terminology from the docs

---

## Enforcement Note
If any of the 4 files are not available or not referenced, you must request them before proceeding.
